## **Description**
The **Script **operator allows to insert, through the configuration settings, RhinoScript code to apply to input data.

> Important

Unlike the **Advanced Script **operator, the **Script **operator does not allow to specify multiple outputs in addition to the predefined output

## **Input**
**Input**

**Data type**

**Description**

**in0**

String

The input node on which to apply the RhinoScript code specified in the configuration settings.

**inâ€¦**

String

N-th input node on which to apply the RhinoScript code specified in the configuration settings.

## **Output**
**Output**

**Data type**

**Description**

**&lt;&gt;out0**

String

The transformed value obtained by applying the specified RhinoScript code.

## **Settings**
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Inputs **section, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add an input node to the list.

- In the **Script **text area, enter the Javascript (RhinoScript) code snippet that you want to apply to the input data.

> Note

For example, the following Javascript (RhinoScript) code splits the input string into various substrings of a predefined maximum length.

**Example: RhinoScript code**

`function split() {
 
valueInput = input.children.get("in0");
if (valueInput == null)
return;
 
inputString = valueInput.get(0).value;
 
var MAXCHARS_PER_LINE = 240;
var MAX_LINES = 15;
var numChar = 0;
var line = "";
var numLines = 0;
var startIndex=0;
var firstPage=1;
var output = "";
 
for (var i=0; i &lt; inputString.length(); i++) {
 
numChar = numChar + 1;
var ch = inputString.charAt(i);
if (ch == 09) {
 ch = " ";
 output = output + inputString.substring(startIndex, i ) + " ";
 startIndex = i + 1;
 
} else if ((ch == 13 || ch == 10)) {
if (startIndex &lt; i - 1)
     output = output + inputString.substring(startIndex, i - 1) + "\t";
i = i + 1;
startIndex = i;
if ((i) &lt; inputString.length() ) {
 
if (inputString.charAt(i) == 10) {
    i = i + 1;
startIndex = i;
}
}
 
 
numChar = 0;
numLines = numLines + 1;
 
} else if (numChar == MAXCHARS_PER_LINE) {
 
line = inputString.substring(startIndex, i + 1);
var eol = line.lastIndexOf(" ");
 
if (eol &gt; 0) {
 
output = output + inputString.substring(startIndex, startIndex + eol + 1);
startIndex = startIndex + eol;
i = startIndex;
 
} else  {
 
output = output + inputString.substring(startIndex, i + 1);
startIndex = 1 + i;
}
 
numChar = 0;
numLines = numLines + 1;
 
}
 
if (numLines == MAX_LINES) {
 
node = helper.createNode();
node.value = output;
helper.addNode(node);
numLines =0;
 
output = "";
 
if (firstPage==1) {
MAX_LINES = 3 * MAX_LINES;
firstPage = 0;
}
}
}
 
if (startIndex &lt; inputString.length()) {
 
line = inputString.substring(startIndex);
node = helper.createNode();
node.value = output + line;
helper.addNode(node);
}
 
}
 
split();`
- Click **Apply **to confirm.

> Tip

To rename an input node, click on its name to edit it.

To remove an input node from the list, move your mouse over it and click ![](data:image/png;base64,) in the **Action **column; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)
